<HL> Magna Group Finishes Mergers</HL>
<DD> 09/02/87</DD>
<SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO>
<IN> FGBI MAGI
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
BANKS, THRIFT INSTITUTIONS (BNK) </IN>
<DATELINE> BELLEVILLE, Ill.  </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Magna Group Inc., a bank holding company, said it completed its previously announced mergers with First Granite Bancorp. 
Inc., Granite City, Ill., and Firstplace Financial Corp., Lincoln, Ill. 

   Magna Group bought First Granite for stock valued at $26 million and paid $11.3 million in cash for Firstplace Financial. 

</TEXT>
